Bit.Name: chip_cpbk_y_sign
Bit.Description: 0:Chip public key Y is positive - 1: Chip Public key Y is negative

Bit.Name: stkeyprov_ecies_ok
Bit.Description: Status of ECIES ST key provisionning when it was attempted

Bit.Name: stkeyprov_hwkey_done
Bit.Description: 0: HWKEY not provisionned - 1: HWKEY was provisioned"

Bit.Name: Security counter
Bit.Description: Security counter involved in product ID for chip certificate verification by HSM-OEM in SSP context

Bit.Name: st_pub_key_id
Bit.Description: ST ECDSA Public Key ID (ST Key Instance fuse part) involved in productID for chip certificate verification by HSM-OEM in RSSe_prov context

Bit.Name: no_cpu_pll
Bit.Description: "0: PLLs for CPU/AXI are enable for cold boot. 1: PLLs for CPU/AXI are not enable for cold boot"

Bit.Name: no_data_cache
Bit.Description: 0:Data cache is used by bootrom 1:Data cache is not used by bootrom

Bit.Name: boot_source_disable
Bit.Description: Disable boot source 0x1: FMC 0x2: QSPI NOR 0x4: eMMC 0x8: SD 0x10: UART

Bit.Name: dont_boot_on_cfm_tamper
Bit.Description: HSE frequency 0: boot on confirmed tamper 1: do not boot on confirmed tamper

Bit.Name: oem_fsbla_monotonic_counter
Bit.Description: [1-0xFFFF] -> [1-32] : Value of monotonic counter is X where X is position of the most significant bit at 1.

Bit.Name: fmc_for_hw_reset
Bit.Description: 0: Use software procedure to reset FMC. 1: use RCC to reset FMC.

Bit.Name: HSE value
Bit.Description: 0: HSE is autodetected 1: 24 MHz, 2: 25 MHz, 3: 26 MHz, 4: 19.2 MHz, 5: 40 MHz, 6: 48 MHz

Bit.Name: snand_need_plane_select_1
Bit.Description: 0:SPI NAND plane select not need, 1:SPI NAND plane select is needed

Bit.Name: nand_nb_of_blocks_1
Bit.Description: Number of blocks in unit of 256 blocks

Bit.Name: nand_block_size_1
Bit.Description: 0:64 pages per block, 1:128 pages per block 2:256 pages per block

Bit.Name: pnand_param_stored_in_otp
Bit.Description: 0:No, 1:Nand parameters define in bank1 or bank2,

Bit.Name: secure_boot
Bit.Description: 0 (unlocked):chip is in CLOSED_UNLOCKED state. Secure boot is not enforced (FSBL authentication is not mandatory) ? [1-15] (locked): chip is in CLOSED_LOCKED state. Secure boot is enforced (FSBL authentication is mandatory)

Bit.Name: prov_done
Bit.Description: 0 : RSSE provisioning is not done? [1-15] : RSSE provisioning is done

Bit.Name: debug_lock
Bit.Description: Lock debug enabling until next reset when chip is CLOSED-LOCKED

Bit.Name: otp_prov_done
Bit.Description: 0 : RSSe OTP provisioning is not done

Bit.Name: oem_fsblm_monotonic_counter
Bit.Description: [1-0xFFFF] -> [1-32] : Value of monotonic counter is X where X is position of the most significant bit at 1.

Bit.Name: snand_need_plane_select_2
Bit.Description: 0:SPI NAND plane select not need, 1:SPI NAND plane select is needed

Bit.Name: nand_nb_of_blocks_2
Bit.Description: Number of blocks in unit of 256 blocks

Bit.Name: nand_block_size_2
Bit.Description: 0:64 pages per block, 1:128 pages per block 2:256 pages per block

Bit.Name: rng_htcr_value
Bit.Description: "0 (no) : RNG use default value ? 1 (yes) : RNG use BOOTROM_CONFIG4/5/6 if not 0

Bit.Name: ospi_io_speed_ovrw
Bit.Description: 0: OSPI io speed is not overwritten by otp configuration - 1: OSPI io speed is overwritten by otp configuration

Bit.Name: A coefficient
Bit.Description: No calibration: 3C. Mode 1 calibration: 1C (0 to 70) and 1.25C (-40 to 125)

Bit.Description: raw data acquired by ADC1 at remperature of 30C VDDA=+VREF= 1.
